subject: RE: [junit] RE: Is there a tool which generates JUnit-teststubs?
msgSnippet: ... Sort of.  A rather porous safety net.  Perhaps better than nothing but maybe much worse than nothing.  It could give you a false sense of security.
messageBody:
> One, in general? Automatically-generated tests could help by
> providing a refactoring safety net before the programmer was
> able to understand and therefore craft by hand the same tests.

Sort of. A rather porous safety net. Perhaps better than nothing but maybe
much worse than nothing. It could give you a false sense of security.
